author: @SimoneIovane
text: I agree with all the encoding you treated, however I got doubts on assigning  an ordinal label based on the mean value of the output. By doing this you are setting the distance between levels to one, while in reality, based on the output mean, some level might be close than others, with distances less than or more than 1. What do you think? I would also point out the risk of data leak in case of mean encoding, for this reason I'd add a random noise to the mean
